Rivers State Governor, Nyesom Wike, has redeemed his pledge of N280m to families of the 14 security operatives murdered by gunmen during attacks on security formations in parts of Rivers State. Wike had during a condolence visit to the state Commissioner of Police, Friday Eboka, last Monday, announced the donation of N20m to each family of officers killed by gunmen. The cheques were presented to11 widows of the police officers at the state police command, two bereaved family members of men of the Nigerian Air Force at the Nigerian Air Force Base, and one widow of Nigeria Security and Civil Defense Corp official in Port Harcourt on Monday. The governor, represented by the Secretary to the State Government, Dr Tammy Danagogo, said the gesture was in fulfilment of his promise to alleviate the plight of the widows and their children. A statement by the media aide to the Rivers State SSG, Julianna Masi reads partly,” His Excellency, Governor Nyesom Wike deeply sympathize with you. “He wants you to know that your husbands and fathers did not die in vain but died for their fatherland and God will certainly take care of all that concerns them. “The governor has asked us to bring this token of N20m each to the widows and children of the deceased security personnel. “Our role as a government is to always identify with people who make sacrifices for the good of humanity, the good of Nigeria and the state. No doubt your husbands are some of those who made such sacrifices along with several officers who are doing same.” Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com